Yes. That's right, Emil.

991
01:18:31,532 --> 01:18:34,438
<i>Alfred sat all evening
on the bench...</i>

992
01:18:34,533 --> 01:18:37,626
<i>and had Emil on his lap.</i>

993
01:18:37,939 --> 01:18:40,524
<i>He helped him, when
he had to throw up,</i>

994
01:18:40,634 --> 01:18:43,954
<i>and consoled him when he
wept over his wickedness.</i>

995
01:18:44,376 --> 01:18:46,876
<i>Emil had heard
that he was drunk,</i>

996
01:18:47,048 --> 01:18:49,727
<i>but he didn't know
how it had happened.</i>

997
01:18:49,752 --> 01:18:53,032
<i>He didn't know that
cherries, when they ferment,</i>

998
01:18:53,057 --> 01:18:57,177
<i>are full of the stuff that
can make you drunk.</i>

999
01:18:57,232 --> 01:19:00,152
Listen! Let me tell
you something.

1000
01:19:00,560 --> 01:19:02,397
The Svenssons in Katthult.

1001
01:19:02,429 --> 01:19:05,021
Emil, the villain, got drunk...

1002
01:19:05,046 --> 01:19:07,061
and slaughtered all the hens.

1003
01:19:07,086 --> 01:19:09,766
Such misery. Such misery!

1004
01:19:11,041 --> 01:19:13,840
<i>The sun went
down, it was dark.</i>

1005
01:19:13,920 --> 01:19:16,348
<i>The moon looked down
at Katthult farm,</i>

1006
01:19:16,457 --> 01:19:20,177
<i>and Alfred still
had Emil in his arm.</i>

1007
01:19:21,482 --> 01:19:23,402
So how are you, Emil?

1008
01:19:23,568 --> 01:19:25,935
I'm still alive.

1009
01:19:25,960 --> 01:19:28,920
But if I die, you'll get Lukas.

1010
01:19:29,000 --> 01:19:32,289
Oh. Nobody died of it yet.

1011
01:19:32,314 --> 01:19:34,674
You can believe me, Emil.

1012
01:19:40,040 --> 01:19:42,024
Listen! Listen! Hey!

1013
01:19:42,049 --> 01:19:46,489
Emil from Katthult...
He got drunk. I know!

1014
01:19:46,920 --> 01:19:49,920
Did you hear?
Emil got drunk.

1015
01:19:50,000 --> 01:19:52,520
- Yes.
- And killed all the hens.

1016
01:19:52,545 --> 01:19:54,520
Come here! Come here!

1017
01:19:54,600 --> 01:19:57,132
Emil from Katthult
farm got drunk...

1018
01:19:57,157 --> 01:19:59,757
and slaughtered all the hens.

1019
01:20:30,787 --> 01:20:33,107
You poor limping Lotte.

1020
01:20:33,992 --> 01:20:36,593
Oh, goodness gracious!

1021
01:20:43,090 --> 01:20:45,815
<i>Ida didn't know what to think.</i>

1022
01:20:45,840 --> 01:20:47,910
<i>Perhaps she had magic hands.</i>

1023
01:20:47,935 --> 01:20:52,208
<i>Yes, perhaps she could bring
back the dead with her hands.</i>

1024
01:20:54,400 --> 01:20:57,760
Hocus-pocus...

1025
01:20:59,207 --> 01:21:00,852
now you're no longer dead.

1026
01:21:00,877 --> 01:21:05,317
The hens had
only fainted with fright,

1027
01:21:05,356 --> 01:21:07,236
when the piglet ran after them.

1028
01:21:07,261 --> 01:21:09,430
That's something hens do.

1029
01:21:11,058 --> 01:21:13,659
Hocus-pocus...

1030
01:21:20,562 --> 01:21:22,962
Hocus-pocus...

1031
01:21:33,080 --> 01:21:35,480
Hocus-pocus...

1032
01:21:42,600 --> 01:21:45,560
Hocus-pocus...

1033
01:21:49,149 --> 01:21:51,429
Hocus-pocus...

1034
01:21:54,442 --> 01:21:57,402
Hocus-pocus...

1035
01:22:10,900 --> 01:22:14,907
Just imagine: I've brought
all the hens back to life.

1036
01:22:23,571 --> 01:22:26,657
<i>The next morning everyone
was on their feet again:</i>

1037
01:22:26,682 --> 01:22:29,642
<i>Emil and the cock
and the piglet.</i>

1038
01:22:32,580 --> 01:22:35,189
<i>But the cock couldn't
crow for three days,</i>

1039
01:22:35,214 --> 01:22:37,674
<i>although he tried again and again.</i>

1040
01:22:45,416 --> 01:22:47,955
<i>The hens looked so reproachful,</i>

1041
01:22:47,980 --> 01:22:51,500
<i>that he disappeared in
the high grass ashamed.</i>

1042
01:22:54,980 --> 01:22:57,600
You can walk normal again.

1043
01:22:58,355 --> 01:23:02,260
To get drunk with
the piglet and lay down.

1044
01:23:03,148 --> 01:23:05,988
You are a real drunkard!

1045
01:23:09,187 --> 01:23:12,437
<i>Emil's mother wrote in
the blue notebook:</i>

1046
01:23:12,522 --> 01:23:15,201
"God help me with this poor boy."

1047
01:23:15,889 --> 01:23:18,855
"Today he was at least sober."

1048
01:23:20,115 --> 01:23:22,840
<i>But that's not the
end of the story yet.</i>

1049
01:23:22,920 --> 01:23:27,130
<i>In the afternoon a car
came to Katthult.</i>

1050
01:23:27,419 --> 01:23:29,526
<i>There were three
serious-looking gentlemen.</i>

1051
01:23:29,551 --> 01:23:34,040
<i>Three Good-Templars from
Lönneberga, who came to visit Emil.</i>

1052
01:23:34,718 --> 01:23:37,898
<i>Now you certainly don't
know what Good-Templars are.</i>

1053
01:23:38,257 --> 01:23:42,773
<i>But I can tell you that there used
to be such people in Lönneberga...</i>

1054
01:23:42,880 --> 01:23:45,590
<i>and were very
necessary in Smaland.</i>

1055
01:23:45,615 --> 01:23:48,107
<i>The Good-Templars
were determined,</i>

1056
01:23:48,169 --> 01:23:50,247
<i>the stop the horrible drinking,</i>

1057
01:23:50,325 --> 01:23:53,177
<i>which used to make so
many people unhappy...</i>

1058
01:23:53,251 --> 01:23:56,200
<i>and certainly still does so today.</i>

1059
01:23:58,632 --> 01:24:02,699
It has come to our attention that
not everything is in order here.

1060
01:24:02,765 --> 01:24:06,608
- What do you mean, please?
- We are thinking of Emil.

1061
01:24:06,729 --> 01:24:09,510
Did Emil do something? Hm?

1062
01:24:09,826 --> 01:24:12,175
They say he was drunk yesterday.

1063
01:24:13,121 --> 01:24:16,241
Well, listen.
That is exaggerated!

1064
01:24:17,244 --> 01:24:20,111
Surely you have been told
that it came to this,

1065
01:24:20,369 --> 01:24:23,855
because he has tasted cherries
from which I made wine.

1066
01:24:23,880 --> 01:24:26,512
Yes, and it wouldn't hurt,

1067
01:24:26,793 --> 01:24:30,160
when he would listen to a
sermon about soberness.

1068
01:24:30,521 --> 01:24:32,040
Today is a meeting.

1069
01:24:32,120 --> 01:24:37,120
After he got to the taste, it
would only be for his best.

1070
01:24:38,920 --> 01:24:41,295
Well, okay.
Then I'll go with him.

1071
01:24:41,320 --> 01:24:44,835
No way. If necessary,
I'll go with you.

1072
01:24:45,788 --> 01:24:49,545
I made the wine, Anton.
You shall not suffer because of this.

1073
01:24:49,760 --> 01:24:52,920
I will attend your campaign
against the alcohol.

1074
01:24:53,369 --> 01:24:57,840
And I could bring Emil,
should you consider it necessary.

1075
01:24:57,920 --> 01:24:59,480
Come, Anton.

1076
01:24:59,560 --> 01:25:01,552
Yes.

1077
01:25:01,577 --> 01:25:03,457
Goodbye.

1078
01:25:06,577 --> 01:25:08,497
See you.

1079
01:25:19,722 --> 01:25:23,026
Emil didn't mind.

1080
01:25:23,056 --> 01:25:26,547
It could be quite nice
to be among people.

1081
01:25:37,120 --> 01:25:39,640
No, Griseknoen, you're not coming!

1082
01:25:39,720 --> 01:25:41,520
Go home!

1083
01:25:44,240 --> 01:25:46,000
Go home, I said.

1084
01:27:23,509 --> 01:27:26,749
First of all, you didn't
drink one glass...

1085
01:27:31,652 --> 01:27:34,132
and secondly, it was my fault.

1086
01:27:40,000 --> 01:27:42,360
We have seen how alcohol...

1087
01:27:42,440 --> 01:27:44,776
has ruined people's prospects.

1088
01:27:45,480 --> 01:27:50,240
How it turns youthful innocence
into vice and shamelessness...

1089
01:27:50,980 --> 01:27:54,737
and how it lets the power
of manhood vanish.

1090
01:27:56,432 --> 01:27:58,487
So I ask you:

1091
01:27:58,680 --> 01:28:01,480
Will you, Emil Svensson,

1092
01:28:01,851 --> 01:28:06,640
for the rest of your life,
take the vow of sobriety?

1093
01:28:07,212 --> 01:28:09,440
Yes, I could do that.

1094
01:28:10,176 --> 01:28:14,080
Our mission is to warn
people for the consequences...

1095
01:28:14,160 --> 01:28:17,360
Piggy! You shouldn't be here.

1096
01:28:28,442 --> 01:28:31,040
Impossible. What is that?

1097
01:28:31,078 --> 01:28:33,358
This is our piglet.

1098
01:28:34,040 --> 01:28:37,920
Take it out.
A pig doesn't belong here.

1099
01:28:38,000 --> 01:28:41,080
Actually, it must
also take a vow.

1100
01:28:41,160 --> 01:28:45,402
After all, it ate more cherries
than I did. Sit, piggy!

1101
01:28:46,751 --> 01:28:48,775
Yes, good.

1102
01:28:50,750 --> 01:28:53,251
You have to be a good piggy.

1103
01:28:54,412 --> 01:28:56,932
Sit... paw.

1104
01:28:57,044 --> 01:28:59,564
Yes. Good.

1105
01:29:00,410 --> 01:29:04,650
- Here. Because you are so obedient.
- This can't be true!

1106
01:29:04,800 --> 01:29:07,776
<i>Everybody was just
looking at the piglet...</i>

1107
01:29:07,823 --> 01:29:11,080
<i>and they were almost
forgetting about the vow.</i>

1108
01:29:11,160 --> 01:29:15,560
So what about the vow?
Or shall we just forget it?

1109
01:29:15,695 --> 01:29:19,615
...to renounce alcoholic
beverages for all times...

1110
01:29:19,640 --> 01:29:23,320
...to renounce alcoholic
beverages for all times...

1111
01:29:23,400 --> 01:29:26,493
and to help our
fellow human beings...

1112
01:29:26,533 --> 01:29:30,088
and to help our
fellow human beings...

1113
01:29:30,174 --> 01:29:34,520
- that they too become sober.
- that they too become sober.

1114
01:29:34,600 --> 01:29:37,514
Griseknoen, this also
applies to you.

1115
01:30:04,800 --> 01:30:07,640
Well, Emil?
There you are again.

1116
01:30:07,922 --> 01:30:09,977
I've taken a vow.

1117
01:30:10,288 --> 01:30:14,528
I have vowed to be sober
throughout my whole life.

1118
01:30:14,960 --> 01:30:17,746
Then I'll tell you
something, Emil.

1119
01:30:18,051 --> 01:30:22,691
If you do, you'll get
the damn piglet.

1120
01:30:23,677 --> 01:30:25,240
For real?

1121
01:30:25,617 --> 01:30:26,695
Yes.

1122
01:30:26,720 --> 01:30:31,640
Besides, I don't think
there won't be any good ham.

1123
01:30:32,348 --> 01:30:34,708
Oh, thank you, father.

1124
01:30:35,400 --> 01:30:41,000
I would never have drunk
alcohol without the piglet.

1125
01:30:41,705 --> 01:30:45,800
The next day, Mrs. Petrell
came to pick up the wine,

1126
01:30:45,880 --> 01:30:48,453
and Emil's mother was glad,

1127
01:30:48,507 --> 01:30:52,627
that his father was
now on the rye field.

1128
01:31:01,226 --> 01:31:04,946
- Hello, Alma!
- Welcome!

1129
01:31:05,380 --> 01:31:07,100
Welcome.

1130
01:31:07,249 --> 01:31:10,178
- Is the wine ready?
- Yes, it is.

1131
01:31:21,137 --> 01:31:23,973
But what are you doing, Emil?

1132
01:31:23,998 --> 01:31:27,036
I'm supposed to
ensure sobriety.

1133
01:31:27,591 --> 01:31:30,360
And so I thought I'd
start with Mrs. Petrell.

